Thanks to STL able to solve 2 problems very easily



Today solved Two problems:

1. Number of 1Bits (LC-->191)

2. Create Target Array in the Given Order (LC-->1389)


1st Problem : Number of 1Bits
Problem Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-1-bits/

Approach: Using the STL inbulit function Count() able to do in easily by just Using it.

Solution: 

class Solution {
public:
    int hammingWeight(uint32_t n) {
      bitset<32>v(n);
      return v.count();
    }
};

Time Complexity  :  O(N) 
Space Complexity : O(1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2nd Problem : Create Target Array in the Given Order (LC-->1389)
Problem Link : https://leetcode.com/problems/create-target-array-in-the-given-order/

Approach : Using the STL inbulit function insert( ) able to do in easily by just 
Using it.

Solution:
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> createTargetArray(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& index) {


     vector<int> ans;
     for(int i=0;i<index.size();i++){

         ans.insert(ans.begin()+index[i],nums[i]);
     }
    return ans;
  }
};


Time Complexity: O(N*2)
Space Complexity: O(1)


